videos.headline: Kempt floats it to a wide open Butler for the TD
videos.description: Iowa State's Kyle Kempt and Hakeem Butler hook up for a 52-yard scoring strike.

videos.headline: Iowa State fumbles punt for huge loss
videos.description: Punter Colin Downing drops the snap and gets tackled for a big loss, giving Memphis good field position.

videos.headline: Miller takes screen pass in for Memphis score
videos.description: Memphis' Riley Ferguson fires to Anthony Miller who scampers in for a 10-yard touchdown.

videos.headline: Lanning powers in for Cyclones TD
videos.description: Two-way LB Joel Lanning takes it in to the end zone on the 2-yard keeper.

videos.headline: Campbell impressed with his defense in first half
videos.description: Coach Matt Campbell says his Cyclone defense needs to keep up its performance on critical downs in the second half.

videos.headline: Mayhue makes a defender miss on way to Memphis TD
videos.description: Riley Ferguson scrambles and finds Phil Mayhue, who uses a nice juke to get in to the end zone.

videos.headline: Lazard works tip drill to perfection for Iowa State TD
videos.description: Allen Lazard shows off incredible concentration to catch a tipped pass in the back of the end zone.

videos.headline: Montgomery fumbles in end zone for touchback
videos.description: David Montgomery fumbles in the end zone, Iowa State's first lost fumble of the season.

videos.headline: Lanning after Cyclones' Liberty Bowl victory
videos.description: Two-way star Joel Lanning led Iowa State's defense against a high-powered Memphis attack and clinched the game on offense with his legs.

videos.headline: Lazard sets Liberty Bowl record with 10 receptions
videos.description: Allen Lazard led the Iowa State offense with 10 catches for 142 yards and a crazy touchdown as the Cyclones win the Liberty Bowl.

videos.headline: Campbell proud to send out seniors with a win
videos.description: Iowa State coach Matt Campbell expresses gratitude for his senior class who capped off one the best seasons in school history as Liberty Bowl champions.
